cyrus-sasl: The Cyrus SASL (The simple authentication and security layer) 
cyrus-sasl:
cyrus-sasl: SASL is the Simple Authentication and Security Layer, a method for 
cyrus-sasl: adding authentication support to connection-based protocols. To use
cyrus-sasl: SASL, a protocol includes a command for identifying and
cyrus-sasl: authenticating a user to a server and for optionally negotiating
cyrus-sasl: protection of subsequent protocol interactions. If its use is
cyrus-sasl: negotiated, a security layer is inserted between the protocol and
cyrus-sasl: the connection
cyrus-sasl:
cyrus-sasl:
